title: White House to Announce New Cuban Regulations
text:
White House to Announce New Cuban Regulations September 18, 2015 
The White House today is expected to announce regulations that will make it safer for Americans to travel to Cuba. According to reports, the new regulations will allow U.S. companies to establish offices in Cuba for the first time in more than 50 years, and allow airlines and cruise ships to import parts and technology to the country. Though the changes will have no effect on travel restrictions, they are a major step toward the Obama administrationâ€™s continued efforts to ease the embargo with Cuba. 0
